Introduced
Second Regular Session 124th General Assembly (2026)
SENATE RESOLUTION ____
MR. PRESIDENT:
I offer the following resolution and move its adoption:
1 A SENATE RESOLUTION memorializing Alice Wong.
2 Whereas, Alice Wong, an artist, editor,and disability justice
3 activist, passed away on November 14, 2025, at the age of 51;
4 Whereas, Alice was a graduate of Carmel High School,
5 received her bachelor's degree from Indiana University-Purdue
6 University Indianapolis in 1997, and earned a master's degree
7 from the University of California, San Francisco in 2004;
8 Whereas, Alice was deeply dedicated to ensuring the
9 political and cultural visibility of individuals with disabilities,
10 cultivating a vibrant and diverse community rooted in joy,
11 abundance, mutual aid, and care;
12 Whereas, Alice published personal stories that expose
13 ableist attitudes, policies, and practices across a society that
14 pushes disabled people to the margins and shared her own
15 experiences navigating the world as a disabled person with a
16 progressive neuromuscular disease;
2026 DR 3825/DI js

2
1 Whereas, In 2024, Alice was awarded a MacArthur
2 Foundation fellowship, commonly referred to as a "genius
3 grant", for her writing and work on behalf of the disabled
4 community;
5 Whereas, Alice edited two essay collections:Disability
6 Visibility, First-Person Stories from the Twenty-First Century,
7 published in 2020 and Disability Intimacy: Essays on Love,
8 Care, and Desire, published in 2024; and
9 Whereas, Alice is survived by her parents, Henry and
10 Bobby Wong, and her sisters, Emily Wong and Grace Wong:
11 Therefore,
12 Be it resolved by the Senate of the
13 General Assembly of the State of Indiana:
14 SECTION 1. That the Indiana State Senate expresses its
15 sympathy and deepest condolences to the family of Alice
16 Wong.
17 SECTION 2. The Secretary of the Senate is hereby directed
18 to transmit a copy of this Resolution to the family of Alice
19 Wong.
